      <td class="medium">
	<h4>Audio Sermons - Podcasting</h4><br>
	<p><a href="http://phobos.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewPodcast?id=74966870" target="_parent">Subscribe to GCC Podcast in iTunes</a></p>
	
	<p><b>What is Podcasting?</b><br>
	 Podcasting is a method of publishing sound files to the Internet, allowing users to subscribe to a feed and receive new audio files automatically. Podcasting is distinct from other types of audio content delivery because it uses the RSS 2.0 file format. This technique has enabled many producers to create self-published, syndicated radio shows.<br><br>
	Users subscribe to podcasts using "podcatching" software (also called "aggregator" software) which periodically checks for and downloads new content. It can then sync the content to the user's portable music player, hence the portmanteau of Apple's "iPod" and "broadcasting". Podcasting does not require an iPod; any digital audio player or computer with the appropriate software can play podcasts. (from <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Podcasting" target="_blank">wikipedia.com</a>)</p>

	<p><b>What is the difference between downloading a sermon and using Podcasting?</b><br>
	Podcasting allows you to automatically sync your iPod with the sermons that we have online. Using the podcatching software with iTunes, you can immediately download and sync your iPod with the sermons.</p><br>

	<p><b><i>HOW TO USE iTUNES TO PODCAST</i></b></p>
	
	<p><b>Step 1:</b> Download <a href="http://www.apple.com/itunes/download/" target="_blank">iTunes version 4.9</a> with Podcasting capabilities. Please install depending on your operating system.</p>
	<p><i>*NOTE: You can also find us under <font color="blue">"Audio Sermons - at Grace Covenant Church, Philadelphia, PA - www.gracecovenant.net" in Religion and Spirituality (Christian)</font> in the Podcast directory in iTunes.</i></p>

	<center><img src="http://www.gracecovenant.net/resources/audiosermons/podcast/itunes.jpg" /></center><br>

	<p><b>Step 2:</b> Open iTunes. In the menu bar, select <b>ADVANCED</b>. A menu should appear, select <b>SUBSCRIBE TO PODCAST...</b></p>

	<p><b>Step 3:</b> The following window should appear:</p>
	<center><img src="http://www.gracecovenant.net/resources/audiosermons/podcast/step3a.jpg" /></center>
	<p>Type in the following: <b>http://www.gracecovenant.net/gccpodcast.xml</b></p>
	<center><img src="http://www.gracecovenant.net/resources/audiosermons/podcast/step3.jpg" /></center><br>
	<p>Click OK.</p>

	<p><b>Step 4:</b> The following window should appear in iTunes:</p>
	<center><img src="http://www.gracecovenant.net/resources/audiosermons/podcast/step4.jpg" /></center><br>
	<p>You should now be subscribed to our Podcast. iTunes will automatically sync audio sermons to your play list when we upload.</p>

	<p>Enjoy and God bless.</p>

	<p>Please email <font color="blue">web@gracecovenant.net</font> if there are problems or suggestions you'd like to see in our podcasts of sermons.</p>

	</td>
